		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd like to add PC-FX MJPEG decoding to Mednafen, the emulator, but I can't figure out what the values of the internal Huffman tables are(they are static, in the chip).  There is one piece of software, mixplay, at <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://home.highway.ne.jp/soltin/mixplay.html">http://home.highway.ne.jp/soltin/mixplay.html</a><!-- m --> that has the Huffman tables in it, but I can't figure out how to convert them to the format I need to use(16 lengths + code table)...  The Magic Engine-FX author reverse-engineered mixplay, but it was too overwhelming when I tried to debug it myself(darn x86 assembly!).
<br />
<br />Does anyone know how to construct a JPEG bytestream that, when decoded by a JPEG decoder, will reveal bits of the Huffman tables used to decode, in the decoded graphics?

		

